overview: The user initiated a request for a code review of a sleep
  questionnaire application. The primary goal was to verify that the existing
  codebase adhered to all specified acceptance criteria. The assistant began by
  thoroughly reviewing the project's documentation, specifically
   and , to establish a clear
  understanding of the expected features and functionalities. This included
  identifying core functionalities like interactive forms, report generation,
  and data handling, as well as specific questionnaire sections, conditional
  logic, and sleep disorder detection algorithms. Following the documentation
  review, the assistant proceeded to examine critical parts of the application's
  source code. This involved inspecting data types, validation logic, the main
  questionnaire form component, individual section components (e.g., for
  daytime, night-time, and nightmares), and API routes responsible for handling
  responses, generating CSV exports, and creating PDF reports. The review aimed
  to provide a comprehensive overview of the application's structure and its
  alignment with the documented requirements.
